{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0b0cba4e-9b27-4770-ad12-164d3c0d2b5b","content":"Here's what to address in each snippet:\n\n**1. Form1.cs — `ContextMenu`/`MenuItem` removed**\n\nThese have been obsolete-as-error since .NET 7 (`WFDEV003`/`WFDEV004`) and are removed in .NET 10. Replace with the `Strip` equivalents:\n\n```csharp\nvar menu = new ContextMenuStrip();\nmenu.Items.Add(new ToolStripMenuItem(\"Open\", null, OnOpen));\n```\n\n**2. ImageProcessor.cs — Exception type changed**\n\nGDI+ historically threw `OutOfMemoryException` for invalid/corrupt images. In .NET 10, `System.Drawing` now throws `ArgumentException` instead. Your `catch (OutOfMemoryException)` will silently miss bad files:\n\n```csharp\ncatch (ArgumentException ex)\n{\n    logger.LogError(ex, \"Invalid image format\");\n}\n```\n\nOr catch both if you need to support shared libraries targeting older runtimes.\n\n**3. MainWindow.xaml — Empty definitions + missing resource**\n\n- Empty `<Grid.ColumnDefinitions/>` and `<Grid.RowDefinitions/>` are no-ops — remove them for clarity.\n- `{DynamicResource MissingKey}` — ensure `MissingKey` is defined in a resource dictionary. WPF in .NET 10 emits binding-failure diagnostics that will surface this at runtime. The `TextBlock` will render blank.\n\n**4. Additional mentions:**\n\n- **StatusStrip**: Default render mode switched to `ToolStripRenderMode.System` in .NET 9. If you were already on .NET 9 you've handled this; if not, explicitly set `statusStrip.RenderMode = ToolStripRenderMode.Professional` to preserve the old look.\n- **TreeView checkboxes**: .NET 10 improved checkbox accessibility handling — verify your `AfterCheck`/`BeforeCheck` event logic still behaves correctly, as state change events may fire differently during initialization.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"da06b9f5-1018-4fd3-8bc3-b001a317c93c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a .NET 9 Windows desktop app to .NET 10. They want to know